126	/// latch-to-leader floor contract: a lagging publisher's strictly-older BBO must never appear out of
127	/// order on the wire, but the leader's distinct BBO changes that share a `source_ts` (real intra-tick
128	/// updates) are kept, so the sequence is non-decreasing, NOT strictly increasing. Fails (proving the
129	/// assertion bites) if the floor is bypassed and an older quote is emitted.
