159	    // changes at a non-decreasing floor. On THIS window latch-to-leader emits the same 4468 as the
160	    // prior merge floor: the faster publisher leads nearly every tick and carries the distinct
161	    // content, so its leader series already covers the full set — latch only drops a sample when the
162	    // *slower* publisher leads a tick yet the faster has extra content, which doesn't occur here (the
163	    // latch drop itself is exercised directly by the `StalenessFloor`/`admit_quote` unit tests). The
164	    // count sits far above a strict one-per-tick watermark (~417, which over-drops real intra-tick
165	    // changes). Observed: 4468.
